														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1269523">
									

<p>This is&#8230; Well.</p>
<p>Awful, in the way that only a piece of fiction themed around a female character implied to enjoy being raped that was written entirely by men can be. You've pretty much taken a steaming dump on subtlety and characterization with this one, and I'm heavily disappointed.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I'm not so sure I &quot;came with&quot; these double-Ds, if you know what I mean.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Who needs to act sweet when you have a nature like mine?</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>I don't need to sugarcoat or forget. I keep my distance from the emotions, sure, but I remember all of it. I remember how he raped me over and over again, and how when he got tired of my natural orifices he cut new ones. I remember how he'd cut off my fingers and toes and then sew them back on, and how he moved up to my other body parts when he got bored with those. What he did with my eyes and my lips…</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yeah. Way to convincingly write a deep and interesting character, there, guys.</p>
<p>Downvoted. If I wanted to read bad one handed fanfic I wouldn't be on this wiki.</p>

							</div>

								
					
