															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kenneth1221" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1813809); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1813809&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163639" alt="kenneth1221" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1813809)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kenneth1221" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1813809); return false;" >kenneth1221</a></span> <span class="odate time_1390193872 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Jan 2014 04:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1940493">
									

<p>I find it interesting how Ms. Sweetie thinks the one person behind the Wondertainment name has to have a penis, and the most defining piece of characterization for Dr. Wondertainment is of &quot;Isabel Helga Anastasia Parvati Wondertainment V, PhD.&quot;</p>
<p>I know, I know, there is no canon, but the idea of that particular Dr. Wondertainment trying to make Ms. Sweetie stupider is very revealing. Maybe the board of directors is primarily male, or maybe she's just that distant from reality.</p>
<p>Either way, I like the series as a whole.</p>

							</div>

								
					
