    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-1940508">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-1940508">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,1940508)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-1940508">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=388108&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163639" alt="Djoric" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=388108)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;" >Djoric</a></span> <span class="odate time_1390194969 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Jan 2014 05:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1940508">
									

<p>I can safely say that Isabel is not the Wondertainment who made the Misters. She's far too innocent of mind for that. But, there are/have been a great many other Wondertainments, and Wondertainment has always been a sort of trickster god. One of them might have done it.</p>
<p>Alternatively, the Little Misters carry the branding, but weren't actually designed by Wondertainment.</p>
<p>Of course this is just my 2 cents, applicable only towards my interpretation of Wondertainment.</p>

							</div>

								
					
